posts.name: Kevin
posts.cooked:
We are trying to integrate photonvision with the ctre autogenerated swerve. We’ve created the photon pose estimator and are attempting to feed it from our camera, using the 2024 field map and 2024 speaker since we still have it assembled. It returns the same exact pose every tick for each tag. I’ve driven sideways, forwards and backwards, and rotated, with nothing changing.

Github Link (feature-pv branch) Help please

posts.name: Kyle Burman
posts.cooked: Try changing your PoseStrategy from PoseStrategy.AVERAGE_BEST_TARGETS to PoseStrategy.MULTI_TAG_PNP_ON_COPROCESSOR

posts.name: Kevin
posts.cooked: I tried this and now the optional for posedata is empty every time.

posts.name: Brian
posts.cooked: Try changing the line var latest results =camera.getUnreadResults() to camera.getLatestResults()

Something to try indeed, but the current docs reccomend getUnreadResults() as you cant miss/duplicate results. image 1490×185 27.4 KB

posts.name: Jeffrey Morris
posts.cooked: Make sure the camera can actually see multiple tags or also set the fallback strategy

posts.name: Brian
posts.cooked: Have you checked the camera configurations themselves? Is it named consistently with your code, 3d mode is turned on (for multitag, 3d mode or whatever its called is necessary), can it detect tags when you go into the web client, and so on. Im guessing the reason its empty during multitag is due to the 3d mode, but that doesn’t exactly solve your original issue…

posts.name: Kevin
posts.cooked: Just set this, not sure it made a difference but I didn’t know fallback strategies existed so thanks lol

posts.name: Kevin
posts.cooked: We can’t get 3d mode on, is that because we haven’t calibrated with a charuco board?

posts.name: Jeffrey Morris
posts.cooked: Yes you need a fallback for multi tag when theres only one

posts.name: Jeffrey Morris
posts.cooked: Yes, you have to calibrate for 3D, check the docs.
